{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"flowered-vertical-discus","description":"## What\n\n`docs/output-schemas.md` points readers at a source path that no longer exists and\ndescribes a bash shell-out design that was removed. It says the machinery \"lives in\none place — `src/rebar/_engine/ticket_output.py` … the bash commands shell into it\"\n(lines ~23-25) and references the bash emitter again (~line 80).\n\nReality on `origin/main`:\n- `src/rebar/_engine/ticket_output.py` does not exist.\n- The parser lives at `src/rebar/_engine_support/output.py` (`parse_output`,\n  `error_envelope`) and is called **in-process** — there is no bash shell-out.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `docs/output-schemas.md` cites the correct module path\n      (`src/rebar/_engine_support/output.py`).\n- [ ] All \"bash commands shell into it\" / bash-emitter framing is replaced with the\n      accurate in-process description.\n- [ ] The doc no longer references any non-existent `_engine/ticket_output.py` path.\n\nFiles: `docs/output-schemas.md` (lines ~23-25 and ~80).","id":"eba7-4315-0f06-42d4","parent_id":"4191-b4f9-146a-43cd","priority":2,"tags":["docs","p1"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"P1: Fix output-schemas.md stale source path & bash-shelling framing"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783814568844675001,"uuid":"fc6cb424-f325-46f6-8907-d821a0e3ea54"}